sentence: Michael Burstein (Hebrew: מייק בורשטיין‎; born July 1, 1945) is an Israeli-American actor known onstage as Mike Burstyn.
He was born in New York City to the late Yiddish-language actors, Pesach Burstein and Lillian Lux.
His first cousin was Borsch Belt comedian, Jay Lester.
Mike began performing on stage at Yiddish theaters from childhood, in musicals and melodramas produced by his father, Pesach Burstein, especially as part of the Four Bursteins.

He had his own show, De Mike Burstyn Show (1978–1981).
Burstyn appeared on Broadway in Barnum, where he succeeded Jim Dale in the title role.
